titles.short: When you want to, but you cannot
titles.full: When you want to, but you can’t (Cuando quieres y no puedes)

summaries.short: María looks to quench an uncontrollable libido. Esther reaches a career low. Cris turns to strangers to fill the void left by Pablo.
summaries.full: Now five months pregnant, María finds herself consumed by an uncontrollable libido. At Gari’s housewarming, she connects with Xosé - and, later, struggles to get through to Esther, who’s doubting her work more than ever after an unsuccessful night at a modern art market. Increasingly frustrated by Pablo’s emotional distance and absentee fathering, Cris takes her infidelity to the next level.

titles.full: When you don’t want to be alone (Cuando no quieres estar sola)

summaries.short: At their 15-year high school reunion, María and Cris contemplate how far they’ve strayed from the lives they once envisioned for themselves.
summaries.full: As their 15-year high school reunion approaches, María braves prenatal classes and gynecology appointments with Gari, while, thanks to Pablo, Cris finds herself increasingly torn between work and mom duties. At the reunion, they contemplate how far they’ve strayed from the lives they once envisioned for themselves.

titles.short: When you confess to your parents
titles.full: When you confess to your parents (Cuando te confiesas con tus padres)

summaries.short: María attempts to open up to her parents about her pregnancy - but ends up forcing Gari to open up to her instead. Meanwhile, Esther realizes her career and personal growth are stunted.
summaries.full: With Gari and Esther along for the ride, María heads to Tarazona, her hometown, to tell her super-Catholic parents she’s pregnant. But when she finds her mother in the middle of a spiritual crisis, María insists on spending the afternoon meticulously learning Gari’s life story instead. Meanwhile, Esther faces some difficult truths about her career and personal growth, and Gari takes an important step towards full independence.

titles.full: When everything falls apart (Cuando todo se derrumba)

summaries.short: While Esther hits rock bottom on her 40th birthday, María tries to get Gari comfortable with Gustavo, and Cris lets her guard down at home.
summaries.full: On Esther’s 40th birthday, a series of stressful encounters make it clear that she’s lost control of her life, prompting her to go rogue. Meanwhile, María arranges for Gari and Gustavo to get to know each other, and Cris’ string of affairs finally catches up to her.

titles.full: When you take an unexpected path (Cuando tomas un camino inesperado)

summaries.short: María and Gari weigh the risks of having a baby together. Meanwhile, Esther’s social media presence flails, and Cris plays with fire on a dating site.
summaries.full: After María oversteps boundaries with Gari, both contemplate the risks of having a baby together. Later, María anxiously awaits genetic test results, Esther struggles to curate a hip social media presence, and, still thinking of her encounter with a handsome stranger, Cris plays with fire on an extramarital dating site.

titles.full: When you let yourself go (Cuando te dejas llevar)

summaries.short: María’s wedding day is full of surprises that give her, Esther, and Cris some overdue clarity on what they want out of life.
summaries.full: After her wedding leaves Gari feeling insecure, María goes into labor while trying to reassure him. At the hospital, she finally gets some overdue clarity on what she really wants out of life. Meanwhile, Cris and Esther have some transformative realizations of their own.

summaries.short: Rattled to learn that Gari has a disability, María attempts to talk to him and open her mind, while Cris struggles to reignite her marriage’s dwindling flame.
summaries.full: Rattled to learn that Gari has a disability, María heads to a funeral hoping to talk to him and open her mind. Cris struggles to reignite passion with Pablo and balance her responsibilities as a mother with a full plate at work. Esther contemplates joining social media to publicize her art.
